<br>
Your quote, above, indicates that you understand how bad off knights were in the days of Kunark, yet you bemoan the lack of corresponding changes to warriors. By adding corresponding changes to warriors, you would be maintaining the Knight classes at their relative level of worthlessness.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
The large gripe is that warriors not only lost a considerable edge, or preeminance as you put it, but have been rendered almost completely redundant. We all understand the problems with knights and I don't believe anyone wants to take away their gains. In fact, I personally think the SK's need more work. The changes we want are to pure melee only. The upgrades to knights have been in both melee and in spells/mana. This has overbalanced them and relegated warriors to second class citizens at the one and only thing we do. I WANT knights to be our equals in total damage output, and in fact would like to see them outdamage us in any encounter with the undead in both melee and spells...but I want that damage output to come through a combination of spells and melee, not melee alone with respect to non-undead mobs. What neither I, nor most every other warrior wants is yet another item to be introduced that further errodes the warriors place in a group or raid, which is what these shields will do. What I also don't want is for Any class to be able to take anywhere near the same punishment warriors do. A few hundred hit points, with damage mitigation being equal, just isn't enough. No monk should ever be able to come close to taking the damage I can as a warrior...he should Avoid damage a helluva lot better than me, but he sure as hell shouldn't take it as well. To a lesser extent, this should be true of knights, for 2 principle reasons. Number 1, there has to be some tradeoff for having spells else there is no point to not having them as a warrior, and the class is totally useless. Number 2, you have healing abilities whereas the max healing i can get is 100pts from a bp that is out of reach for small guilds or independents and not even available until lvl 50. You can heal yourself if you have to, even in combat, which negates the need to have as many hit points or as much damage mitigation as we should have. By having much higher hp and/or damage mitigation, it also secures our place as being a necessity for raids and desireable for groups without removing the gains knights have been given over the last 2 years. I don't want knights to be worthless...in fact, as a raid leader, I wouldn't think of going to battle without pallies for their lay hands ability and sk's for their ability to quickly get agro on adds and then tank them for enough time for an enchanter to get in a mez, a shaman to get in a slow, or an st to take over.<br>
<br>
I don't even really have a problem with the shields...shields have needed an upgrade since their introduction...they don't function as a shield should. However, in the current incarnation on test, they would give a bonus to classes that don't need  a reduction in damage and increase in agro gaining ability, and further reduce the dps of a class that's already too low. This will put warriors further behind the 8 ball. <br>
<br>
If shields are to go live in their current form then the warrior deficiencies Must be addressed at the same time or we might as well all reroll. The only way we could maintain even a modicum of parity is if our offhand, if it's holding a weapon, were given the same type of agro generating ability, block ability and ac bonus, retroactively as the shields will get. <br>
<br>
This won't fix what's already broken with the warrior class, but at the least it will not introduce an item for which we are not trained to use, will get proficient with at a very slow rate (because we will never use a shield unless we are MT), that must be procured, reduces our dps significantly and removes most of the utility of our class in terms of scalability in raids and desirability in xp groups.<br>
<br>
peace,<br>
Aielman KajiraLiege<br>
