<br>
...If you are &quot;repulsed&quot; by a warriors saying that the one pure melee class ought to be better than hybrid melee at the ONE thing we do, then I submit to you that you should either grow a thicker skin, or stick to the boards that are not for and about warriors. This is our house and we're here to talk about Our issues.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I have a couple of problems with that. First, do you really think there would be <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  any</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> role left for the knights in an xp group if warriors tanked 50% better than they did? Honestly? Secondly, you tell the knights to go mind their own business and stay off your board when you are discussing changes that, if implemented, would have a very large impact on them. That's not very realistic.<br>
<br>
....<br>
<br>
Yes, warriors should tank better than knights do. They already DO tank better than knights do. Warriors have about 15-20% more hp and have higher dodge/parry/riposte caps. The hp difference doesn't mean much in xp groups that don't use CH for healing. It does make a difference when CH is the primary heal. The D/P/R differences always make a difference.<br>
<br>
A knight should be about 90% as effective at tanking as a comparably equipped warrior and do about 75-80% as much damage. When you are looking at big raid mobs, knights are less than 70-80% as effective in tanking due to the part that total hp plays in CH chains and due to the difference in D/P/R caps. That seems fine to me. <br>
<br>
I don't know how damage output plays out at the very high end, but knights should not be doing the same damage as warriors. Personally, I probably do about 60-70% of a similarly equipped warrior, which I think may be a touch low, but I don't have any problems with that. <br>
<br>
My personal opinion is that knights should tank at about 90% effectiveness compared to a warrior for xp stuff, and about 70% as well for CH chain type things. Knight's should do about 75-80% of a warrior's damage output.<br>
<br>
PS, the only time I ever use a shield is when I'm trying to tank nasty as hell stuff.<br>
<br>
EDIT: wanted to add that like Furor, I think that the problem lies not in any disparity between the tanks, but in the growing DPS gap between tanks and damage dealers and the lack of benefit to adding mitigation AC.<br>
<br>
It is the insane damage output of rogues, monks, and to a lesser extent, rangers that is the root of the problem. How many groups want 2 tanks when they could have 1 tank and an extra damage dealer? When the DPS difference between the tanks and damage dealers is so large that choosing between a second tank and a second damage dealing melee is a complete no brainer there is a problem. When you compound that problem by closing the gap in tanking ability between the tanks and the damage dealing melee, you end up with the mess we have now. <p><A href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=14686"> Graal MacBladefury</A><BR>
