No, if you had taken the time to read you would have seen I was talking about a paladin using a aggro spell (hint:stun) which would get the mobs attention far quicker than some warrior in defensive trying to get aggro. I mentioned your heals in a reponse to YOUR comments in a different area entirely (hint: uses of Paladins on raids). of course this is all theory however, and its impossible to say for sure as there are so many different variables on different raids. My scenario is far more viable in my opinion.<br>
<br>
&quot;And no, your avg paladin doesn't do even 90% of a warriors dps, its about 75%.&quot;<br>
<br>
Umm, refer to above about reading. This time though read and understand your own comments. You were talking about tanking (95%) to which I replied 90%.  Where the hell does DPS come in there? Again DPS was mentioned in another area.<br>
<br>
&quot; I would not take a paladin over even the 9th or 10th warrior most likely in a raid. Paladins are low DPS output class with poor healing and no disciplines.&quot;<br>
<br>
Ever been to a raid with AEing mobs? If you had the choice to pick whatever you wanted for a raid why have 10 more warriors when all they bring is damage? Just bring rogues, monks or the real damaging class. Paladins do a @#%$ load more on raids than just DPS. And because of that versatility there is more room for paladins to be useful IMO.<br>
<br>
edit:- for example<br>
<br>
Patch healing MT, healing the fallen up after rezzed, backup rezzers if raid whipes and they manage to camp, secondary tank if things go bad and quick aggro is needed (a paladin can heal himself three times over while holding an add (4 times with LOH, better than defensive on an add IMO)), LOH order on Mt or someone important about to die, AE buffs only they get, ae healing group after damage ae's taking effect, helping with dispells. added DPS to mob and general healing after fight. <br>
<br>
But of course you already knew this, afterall you are the Paladin.<br>
<br>
end edit.<br>
<br>
<br>
&quot;Don't say but yeah our top paladin does higher dps than our 3rrd best warrior in the guild and say that changes things.&quot;<br>
<br>
Our top Paladin does more damage than our top Warrior. Not because of skills mind you, but because Paladin weapons with better ratios are so much easier to come by. So of equivalent gear and level, yes Our Paladin does his fair share damage wise and is up there with the warriors.<br>
<br>
<br>
&quot;The only sad things is I think SK's have it worse than the paladins.&quot;<br>
<br>
Sk's are another class entirely. I agree they could use some upgrades as far as raids are concerned. But No chance you are going to convince me Paladins have it bad. Don't need a post to tell me that (which it didn't, lots seemed to agree with me), I have seen it with my own eyes.<br>
<br>
All this is raid talk mind you, not even exp situations. Its funny that people are telling us we are only supposed to excel for raid situations, then complain that we are better there(which I find mostly baseless).<br>
